<body>
  <p style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 12px;">Hello there! Some more new things in <a href="http://www.getnoodl.es/" style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">Noodles</a> today.</p>
  <ul>
    <li style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; line-height: 1.5;"><a href="http://www.getnoodl.es/announcements/3/#import" style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: underline;">Import from the Web</a></li>
    <li style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; line-height: 1.5;"><a href="http://www.getnoodl.es/announcements/3/#search" style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: underline;">Search</a></li>
    <li style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; line-height: 1.5;"><a href="http://www.getnoodl.es/announcements/3/#sharing" style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: underline;">New sharing, plus un-sharing</a></li>
    <li style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; line-height: 1.5;"><a href="http://www.getnoodl.es/announcements/3/#notes" style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; font-weight: normal; text-decoration: underline;">Add notes while viewing a recipe</a></li>
  </ul>
  <p style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 12px;">As a side note, you can now access Noodles at <a href="http://www.getnoodl.es" style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">http://www.getnoodl.es</a>. I previously had the homepage there, with the app itself at app.getnoodl.es. Now, if you're logged in, you automatically go to your recipes. <a href="http://www.getnoodl.es" style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">Check it out!</a></p>
  <hr style="margin-top: 15px; border-top-style: solid; border-top-color: #C5C5C5; border-width: 1px 0 0;">
  <p style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 12px;"><a id="import" style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;"></a></p>
  <h2 id="import-from-the-web" style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; font-weight: 300 !important;">Import from the Web</h2>
  <p style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 12px;">This has to be one of my favorite features of Noodles. You can now just paste in the URL of a recipe, and Noodles will pull in all the data for you and create your recipe automatically. Currently it supports Epicurious, NYTimes Cooking, Food &amp; Wine, Bon Appetit, and Allrecipes, but if you want another recipe site, you can <a href="https://lachlanjc.typeform.com/to/boO233" style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">request it here</a>.</p>
  <p style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 12px;">To get to this, click the new "link" button right above the recipe add button:</p>
  <p style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 12px;"><img src="https://draftin.com:443/images/25818?token=wKTcZhKcm-hVfqGtGbDfKc9Zj-wkSLGEGtk3iF52nWd1qg2UNHiik8Xw_r7yqbtQcTLtLmM3R9RBi45Pu6Pwino" alt="import-button.png" style="max-width: 85%;"></p>
  <p style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 12px;">You'll get a little window into which to paste your link:</p>
  <p style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 12px;"><img src="https://draftin.com:443/images/25819?token=peJAuWoHEK4kj-_-aKbcWYFpQ031_RcM2DfLvQHskQfjBi6JfJo_2cfL9AKWTsFnmpEsxGp9aTCtpOJioxuwtic" alt="import-modal.png" style="max-width: 85%;"></p>
  <p style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 12px;">and then your recipe appears! I haven't had any issues with it so far, but if you do, please tell me. </p>
  <hr style="margin-top: 15px; border-top-style: solid; border-top-color: #C5C5C5; border-width: 1px 0 0;">
  <p style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 12px;"><a id="search" style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;"></a></p>
  <h2 id="search" style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; font-weight: 300 !important;">Search</h2>
  <p style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 12px;">No more Cmd+F! You can now search your recipes with the search bar above your recipe list. It will search the title and description of your recipes. I've wanted this since launch and it works smoothly now.</p>
  <p style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 12px;"><img src="https://draftin.com:443/images/25815?token=Hs6X5Er5WB4uTvkLYq86X9TeDfFZVYdvde9Nu9cuU9I-rZG5hBrowh_w2MfpJZ2pBSsc5zMQfc8qQLstNTvRh58" alt="search.png" style="max-width: 85%;"></p>
  <hr style="margin-top: 15px; border-top-style: solid; border-top-color: #C5C5C5; border-width: 1px 0 0;">
  <p style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 12px;"><a id="sharing" style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;"></a></p>
  <h2 id="new-sharing,-plus-un-sharing" style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; font-weight: 300 !important;">New sharing, plus un-sharing</h2>
  <p style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 12px;">I've rewritten sharing. URLs are now almost impossible to guess, and the sharing pages themselves look much better. Check one out: <a href="http://www.getnoodl.es/s/nWm7EeR" style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">http://getnoodl.es/s/nWm7EeR</a></p>
  <hr style="margin-top: 15px; border-top-style: solid; border-top-color: #C5C5C5; border-width: 1px 0 0;">
  <p style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 12px;"><a id="notes" style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;"></a></p>
  <h2 id="add-notes-while-viewing-a-recipe">Add notes while viewing a recipe</h2>
  <p style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 12px;">Editing notes used to require going to the edit page, showing the details, adding your notes, and then saving the recipe again &mdash; tedious at best. Now, at the bottom of your recipe you see your notes:</p>
  <p style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 12px;"><img src="https://draftin.com:443/images/25820?token=b1NVqmyCUstZEBHwZXwLAhLckP2yLq3GOYN3HWe4VJE1ulPIAMaaqJPAuGsnp5qSmRKCCh3Ynd7SjCT9CAf5Ccc" alt="notes-view.png" style="max-width: 85%;"></p>
  <p style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 12px;">But you can click on the second tab to edit your notes right there. Just remember to save when you're done!</p>
  <p style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 12px;"><img src="https://draftin.com:443/images/25821?token=0lhrcRVV3WZ6U5Dku81QRgDAqKK5dA6Yq9D8lslu9mikBkXsU8Jbe7pnCnVM9Q5E43yx5XPtgnObzFeUqiC31M0" alt="notes-write.png" style="max-width: 85%;"></p>
  <hr style="margin-top: 15px; border-top-style: solid; border-top-color: #C5C5C5; border-width: 1px 0 0;">
  <p style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 12px;">Enjoy, and keep cooking!</p>
  <p style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 12px;">You can reach out to me on Twitter (<a href="https://twitter.com/lachlanjc" style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">@lachlanjc</a>), or through the official Noodles account, <a href="https://twitter.com/noodlesapp" style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">@noodlesapp</a>. And you can always simply reply to this email.</p>
  <p style="font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #333; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 12px;">-Lachlan</p>
  <p style="color: #9e9e9e; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 12px;">If you'd rather not get these emails, <a href="http://www.getnoodl.es/announcements/unsubscribe/EAY7pdX9/<%= @id %>" style="color: #9e9e9e; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">unsubscribe</a> :(</p>
</body>
